dct_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Druskieniki, sheet K-18. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dct_description_sm: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Druskieniki, Lithuania. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 and Russian belt 5 grids. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Lithuania 1:25,000, German General Staff 1915-16; Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, Sheets 32-37, 1929; 32-38, 1928; 33-37, 1928 and 33-38, 1932. Lithuanian place names from Lietuvos Apgyventos Vietos Census Report, 1925. Road classification in Lithuania taken from Lietuvos Zemelapis, 1:400,000, Lithuanian General Staff, 1933. Road classification in Poland based on British intelligence information.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
